                        <interp inst="t18410510-name-765" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS LARKINS</persName>
                  </hi>. I am barman at the King's Arms, Back-hill, St. George's. I received information, and followed the prisoner—I found him three or four doors from the house, with this can and a bag under his arm—I pursued, calling, "Stop thief"—he immediately began to run—I sat him drop it at the corner of Johnson-street—I took it up, and brought it back—it belongs to my master, Thomas Wilson—I had seen it in the bar three minutes before.</p>
